1
00:00:07,958 --> 00:00:10,083
♪

2
00:00:14,708 --> 00:00:16,458
[maniacal laughter]

3
00:00:16,541 --> 00:00:19,625
[KEERA]
It's simply wonderful!

4
00:00:19,708 --> 00:00:20,833
[KEERA]
Just as I'd expect

5
00:00:20,916 --> 00:00:22,250
from a forbidden Summon

6
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:25,000
that has the power
to destroy the entire world.

7
00:00:25,083 --> 00:00:28,041
[maniacal laughter]

8
00:00:31,541 --> 00:00:32,666
[TAKUMA]
I don't remember seeing

9
00:00:32,750 --> 00:00:34,666
a Summon like
this in Cross Reverie.

10
00:00:34,750 --> 00:00:36,500
I think you
should probably run!

11
00:00:36,583 --> 00:00:37,875
[SHERA] That guardian
deity's been growing

12
00:00:37,958 --> 00:00:39,708
in the royal family
for generations!

13
00:00:39,791 --> 00:00:41,458
Not even you
can defeat it!

14
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:43,875
♪

15
00:00:47,250 --> 00:00:49,125
[roars]

16
00:00:50,125 --> 00:00:52,666
♪

17
00:00:54,416 --> 00:00:55,708
[whimpering]

18
00:00:55,791 --> 00:00:57,458
[DIABLO]
I'm intrigued.

19
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:01,416
[DIABLO]
Everyone, stand back.

20
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:03,750
[DIABLO] I need room
to crush that thing!

21
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:09,541
♪

22
00:02:37,083 --> 00:02:38,458
♪

23
00:02:38,541 --> 00:02:39,791
[growling]

24
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:43,666
[whimpering]

25
00:02:44,666 --> 00:02:45,583
That's it.

26
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:46,833
Attack, Force Hydra.

27
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:48,500
Tear that demon apart!

28
00:02:48,583 --> 00:02:51,000
[roars]

29
00:02:51,083 --> 00:02:52,375
[yelps]

30
00:02:52,458 --> 00:02:53,375
[DIABLO]
Goodness.

31
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:54,250
Looks like
you might need to

32
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:55,791
re-train this one.

33
00:02:56,916 --> 00:02:58,333
[TAKUMA]
I don't recognize this monster

34
00:02:58,416 --> 00:02:59,666
or the flute
he was using

35
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:02,000
to control Shera.

36
00:03:02,083 --> 00:03:03,041
It's possible that

37
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:04,750
planned elements
of Cross Reverie

38
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:06,625
that haven't been
released in the real world

39
00:03:06,708 --> 00:03:08,000
are present here.

40
00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:10,708
Which makes it
that much more exciting.

41
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:12,375
[panting]

42
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:14,500
♪

43
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:16,333
[CELSIOR]
Huh? Isn't that?

44
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:17,833
[panting]

45
00:03:17,916 --> 00:03:18,833
You idiot!

46
00:03:18,916 --> 00:03:20,125
Just give up now!

47
00:03:20,208 --> 00:03:22,625
There's no possible
way for you to win!

48
00:03:22,708 --> 00:03:24,125
[TAKUMA] He's got
a lot of confidence

49
00:03:24,208 --> 00:03:25,375
in this
over-sized lizard,

50
00:03:25,458 --> 00:03:26,791
doesn't he?

51
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:29,291
[DIABLO]
Heaven's Fall!

52
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:30,500
[explosion]

53
00:03:30,583 --> 00:03:33,833
♪

54
00:03:34,916 --> 00:03:36,250
[groaning]

55
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:38,958
♪

56
00:03:40,750 --> 00:03:42,666
[TAKUMA]
It's much weaker than I thought.

57
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,708
Just four of five
more shots left.

58
00:03:44,791 --> 00:03:46,000
[gurgling]

59
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:51,291
[grunts]

60
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:52,583
[TAKUMA]
Regeneration?

61
00:03:52,666 --> 00:03:53,750
That's way too fast.

62
00:03:53,833 --> 00:03:55,208
Is there a glitch?

63
00:03:55,291 --> 00:03:57,500
[DIABLO grunts]

64
00:03:57,583 --> 00:03:59,208
-Come on, Diablo!
-Diablo!

65
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:01,458
That's it,
Force Hydra!

66
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:03,791
Blow the bastard-- [yelps]

67
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:05,916
♪

68
00:04:07,041 --> 00:04:08,541
[TAKUMA]
Dragon's Breath is a purely

69
00:04:08,625 --> 00:04:09,958
elemental attack.

70
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:10,958
Magic Reflection

71
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:12,333
and physical
damage reduction

72
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:14,583
won't counter it.

73
00:04:14,666 --> 00:04:16,041
What I'm
actually worried about

74
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:17,375
is its skills.

75
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:18,833
Summons are
supposed to be limited

76
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:20,416
to just one power.

77
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:23,208
♪

78
00:04:24,208 --> 00:04:25,666
[TAKUMA]
Not this guy.

79
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:29,291
It seems to
have at least two.

80
00:04:29,375 --> 00:04:31,208
[explosions]

81
00:04:34,625 --> 00:04:36,541
[grunts]

82
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:38,833
[TAKUMA]
Ice, Sand, Wind and Fire?

83
00:04:38,916 --> 00:04:40,708
It can't have
that many attacks!

84
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:41,958
Is this just a world

85
00:04:42,041 --> 00:04:43,333
that happens to
resemble Cross Reverie

86
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:45,541
but is actually
totally different?

87
00:04:45,625 --> 00:04:47,166
Yes, yes, that's it!

88
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:49,250
Cower before
my Summon!

89
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,875
Anyone who
gets in my way

90
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:54,083
will be obliterated
by my guardian beast.

91
00:04:54,166 --> 00:04:56,166
[explosions]

92
00:04:58,666 --> 00:05:00,833
[maniacal laughter]

93
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:05,083
♪

94
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:13,083
[TAKUMA]
It has to have a weakness,

95
00:05:13,166 --> 00:05:14,541
but where is it?

96
00:05:14,625 --> 00:05:16,208
[SHERA]
Diablo!

97
00:05:16,291 --> 00:05:18,375
The Force Hydra
has a core on its body

98
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:20,000
that holds
all of its power.

99
00:05:20,083 --> 00:05:21,458
If you can find
and destroy it,

100
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:23,916
that will return it
to its crystal!

101
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,250
[TAKUMA]
Destroy the core.

102
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:26,583
Oh, how convenient

103
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:28,541
that you can remember
something like that?

104
00:05:28,625 --> 00:05:30,041
Only thing is.

105
00:05:30,125 --> 00:05:31,041
She forgot to tell you

106
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:32,041
that the core moves

107
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:33,791
continuously
within its body.

108
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:35,041
So, it won't be that easy

109
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:36,375
for you to find!

110
00:05:36,458 --> 00:05:38,375
[explosions]

111
00:05:38,458 --> 00:05:39,958
♪

112
00:05:40,041 --> 00:05:41,708
[maniacal laughter]

113
00:05:41,791 --> 00:05:42,750
[DIABLO]
You say that

114
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,166
like it's a unique trait?

115
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:45,208
What's that?

116
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:46,708
[DIABLO]
I wasn't planning to

117
00:05:46,791 --> 00:05:48,000
search for it.

118
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:50,208
[echoing]
Matoi Izuna!

119
00:05:50,291 --> 00:05:52,625
[electricity crackling]

120
00:05:52,708 --> 00:05:53,708
[grunts]

121
00:05:56,666 --> 00:05:57,708
[growls]

122
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:03,750
[explosions]

123
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,166
[whimpering]

124
00:06:18,041 --> 00:06:19,208
[gasp]

125
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:22,791
♪

126
00:06:24,375 --> 00:06:25,750
[whimpers]

127
00:06:25,833 --> 00:06:29,000
No. What is this power?

128
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:31,333
This shouldn't be possible.

129
00:06:31,416 --> 00:06:33,041
[gasps]

130
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:34,833
[footsteps approaching]

131
00:06:34,916 --> 00:06:36,791
[REM]
Glad you finally figured it out!

132
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:38,250
I've never
seen anyone

133
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:40,041
beat a summon
that powerful.

134
00:06:40,125 --> 00:06:41,541
You're very impressive.

135
00:06:41,625 --> 00:06:44,875
♪

136
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,083
[gasps]

137
00:06:47,166 --> 00:06:49,666
What the hell are you?

138
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:50,958
[DIABLO]
I am Diablo,

139
00:06:51,041 --> 00:06:53,416
the wild Demon Lord
from another world,

140
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:55,333
where not even
Elves can tame.

141
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:56,250
[KEERA]
You are not!

142
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,625
Shut up!

143
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:59,875
Like I'd really believe
you're a Demon Lord!

144
00:06:59,958 --> 00:07:02,416
I have no problem
proving it to you.

145
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,500
You'll need to pay
for your mistakes.

146
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:06,833
With your pathetic life!

147
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:07,750
[grunts]

148
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:08,833
[clanks]

149
00:07:08,916 --> 00:07:10,666
[DIABLO]
Say your goodbyes, Elf.

150
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,416
-[whimpers]
-Come forth.

151
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,666
Burst Explos--

152
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,916
-Wait! Don't do it!
-[grunts]

153
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,041
But, why?

154
00:07:18,125 --> 00:07:19,458
If you're
under his spell,

155
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:21,125
you need to
snap out of it!

156
00:07:22,083 --> 00:07:24,458
It's really me.

157
00:07:24,541 --> 00:07:25,416
[scoffs]

158
00:07:26,583 --> 00:07:27,708
No one
hates my brother

159
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:29,291
more than I do.

160
00:07:29,375 --> 00:07:31,250
He's the worst.

161
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,291
But, still.

162
00:07:32,375 --> 00:07:33,333
I can't change the fact

163
00:07:33,416 --> 00:07:34,500
that he's family.

164
00:07:35,458 --> 00:07:37,166
He's still the one
who made me smile

165
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:38,333
when we were little.

166
00:07:39,541 --> 00:07:40,666
[scoffs]

167
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:44,333
[gasps]

168
00:07:44,416 --> 00:07:46,500
[DIABLO]
Are you sure about this?

169
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,333
[sighs]

170
00:07:48,416 --> 00:07:50,416
Thank you very much.

171
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:51,916
And I'm sorry.

172
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,333
[grunts softly]

173
00:07:53,416 --> 00:07:54,875
[gasp]

174
00:07:54,958 --> 00:07:56,916
♪

175
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,666
[GALFORD]
It defeats the entire purpose

176
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,416
if you decide to spare him.

177
00:08:03,916 --> 00:08:05,958
[KEERA grunts]
Shera.

178
00:08:08,458 --> 00:08:09,708
[head thuds]

179
00:08:09,791 --> 00:08:10,666
[body thuds]

180
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:11,875
[gasp]

181
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:12,875
[screams]

182
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:13,916
Master Keera!

183
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:15,000
[gasp]

184
00:08:15,083 --> 00:08:18,458
♪

185
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:25,250
[DIABLO]
Galford?

186
00:08:26,458 --> 00:08:29,583
♪

187
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:32,000
[whimpers]

188
00:08:32,083 --> 00:08:33,500
[gasps]

189
00:08:33,583 --> 00:08:36,000
Galford.
What are you doing here?

190
00:08:36,083 --> 00:08:37,875
You'll pay for that!

191
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,041
[CELSIOR grunts]

192
00:08:40,375 --> 00:08:42,333
This is what we call a war.

193
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:43,458
It started the moment

194
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:45,083
that Elf prince
sent his troops

195
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:47,625
into another
nation's territory.

196
00:08:47,708 --> 00:08:48,916
[GALFORD]
He should have known

197
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,958
that he was gambling
with his own life.

198
00:08:51,041 --> 00:08:52,166
[grunting]

199
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:54,875
[footsteps approaching]

200
00:08:54,958 --> 00:08:56,458
Exterminate
the Elven troops

201
00:08:56,541 --> 00:08:58,041
scattered
throughout the forest!

202
00:08:58,125 --> 00:08:59,708
Capture the princess!

203
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:00,583
You may eliminate

204
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,250
all who try to interfere!

205
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:04,458
[DIABLO]
Hold on.

206
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:06,458
Was this part of
your plan all along?

207
00:09:06,541 --> 00:09:08,125
You ordered me
to fight the Elves,

208
00:09:08,208 --> 00:09:09,791
in the name of Faltra,

209
00:09:09,875 --> 00:09:11,083
so that you
would be justified

210
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:13,041
in seizing Greenwood?

211
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:14,791
If you intend
to cause a scene,

212
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,875
I'll be forced
to eliminate you.

213
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:20,083
♪

214
00:09:20,166 --> 00:09:21,166
[gasping]

215
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:22,125
[SHERA whimpers]

216
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:25,500
♪

217
00:09:25,583 --> 00:09:27,750
[TAKUMA gasps]
What is this?

218
00:09:27,833 --> 00:09:29,958
-[explosion]
-[grunts]

219
00:09:30,041 --> 00:09:31,750
Another spell
I don't know.

220
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:33,833
It's been nothing
but surprises all day.

221
00:09:33,916 --> 00:09:35,208
It's Ritual Magic

222
00:09:35,291 --> 00:09:37,833
designed to capture
more powerful monsters.

223
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:38,958
I hope you'll take it

224
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:40,791
as a compliment
on your strength.

225
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:42,000
[ALICIA]
Sir Galford.

226
00:09:42,083 --> 00:09:42,916
Hmm?

227
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,416
Please explain yourself.

228
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,000
What is
the meaning of this?

229
00:09:46,083 --> 00:09:47,541
[GALFORD]
I'm the Lord of Faltra,

230
00:09:47,625 --> 00:09:49,041
which means
some of my duties

231
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:50,416
include crushing invaders

232
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,875
and protecting my people.

233
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,250
That's fine,

234
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:55,000
but you're killing those
who have surrendered!

235
00:09:55,083 --> 00:09:56,416
[GALFORD]
Is that so?

236
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,541
It doesn't
look as though

237
00:09:57,625 --> 00:09:59,291
they've surrendered to me.

238
00:09:59,375 --> 00:10:01,500
Is my military judgment
being questioned

239
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:03,458
by a lone imperial knight?

240
00:10:03,541 --> 00:10:04,500
You know it's wrong

241
00:10:04,583 --> 00:10:06,250
and I'm going to stop you!

242
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:07,791
Hmm.

243
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:09,125
How do you
plan to do that

244
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:11,125
when your sword
has no blade?

245
00:10:11,208 --> 00:10:12,458
Huh?

246
00:10:12,541 --> 00:10:13,875
-[gasps]
-[clatters]

247
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:15,083
[grunts]

248
00:10:15,166 --> 00:10:17,250
♪

249
00:10:18,875 --> 00:10:20,125
No way,

250
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:22,500
it's like he
did it with his mind.

251
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:24,125
[TAKUMA]
Damn, he's fast!

252
00:10:24,208 --> 00:10:26,291
Those movements are on a
completely different level

253
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:28,958
than other soldiers
and adventurers.

254
00:10:29,041 --> 00:10:31,083
He's surpassed
all Human limits!

255
00:10:31,166 --> 00:10:33,416
Definitely above
level one hundred!

256
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,666
♪

257
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:36,916
[GALFORD]
You're free to return

258
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,041
to the capital
and give your report.

259
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:40,208
[ALICIA gasps]

260
00:10:40,291 --> 00:10:41,500
[GALFORD]
Just know that His Majesty

261
00:10:41,583 --> 00:10:44,000
will always side
with the stronger person.

262
00:10:46,416 --> 00:10:47,291
[grunts]

263
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:49,583
[TAKUMA]
If this continues,

264
00:10:49,666 --> 00:10:51,125
it won't just be Shera.

265
00:10:51,208 --> 00:10:53,500
Rem and Alicia
will be in danger, too.

266
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:57,041
It's time

267
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:59,375
to sense the flow
of magic power.

268
00:11:01,791 --> 00:11:03,208
I got this!

269
00:11:03,291 --> 00:11:06,416
This is nothing compared
to the enslavement collars.

270
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,250
Where is the power
here centered?

271
00:11:09,583 --> 00:11:11,250
Are we ready to begin?

272
00:11:11,333 --> 00:11:12,458
Grab the princess.

273
00:11:12,541 --> 00:11:14,458
Kill any who interfere.

274
00:11:14,541 --> 00:11:15,375
[KNIGHTS]
Yes, sir!

275
00:11:15,458 --> 00:11:16,500
[whimpers]

276
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:17,458
[grunts]

277
00:11:19,125 --> 00:11:20,750
[TAKUMA]
There's the yarn ball!

278
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:22,791
That's the center
of magic power.

279
00:11:22,875 --> 00:11:24,000
Hurry!

280
00:11:24,958 --> 00:11:26,250
[explosion]

281
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:31,041
♪

282
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:32,666
Didn't expect that.

283
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:34,625
So you
unraveled the barrier?

284
00:11:34,708 --> 00:11:35,875
[gasps]

285
00:11:35,958 --> 00:11:37,541
I knew he'd do it.

286
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:39,208
[metal clanking]

287
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:42,125
[GALFORD]
Stand back.

288
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:45,291
[GALFORD]
I suppose I should have

289
00:11:45,375 --> 00:11:46,750
dealt with you right away.

290
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:50,625
Wouldn't have
worked for you.

291
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:52,083
You were
hoping I'd wear out

292
00:11:52,166 --> 00:11:53,375
fighting the Elves,

293
00:11:53,458 --> 00:11:55,208
and then
you would invade.

294
00:11:55,291 --> 00:11:57,583
Also known as a "strategy."

295
00:11:57,666 --> 00:11:58,833
Not that I'd expect you

296
00:11:58,916 --> 00:11:59,958
to understand.

297
00:12:00,041 --> 00:12:01,708
I wasn't trying to.

298
00:12:01,791 --> 00:12:03,291
Everyone knows that insults

299
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:04,208
from an opponent

300
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:05,708
are praise to a soldier.

301
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:07,541
The only way you'll
insult anyone

302
00:12:07,625 --> 00:12:10,166
is by showing your face
after I destroy it.

303
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:11,375
[chuckles]

304
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:19,666
[echoing]
Explosion!

305
00:12:21,583 --> 00:12:22,583
[DIABLO grunts]

306
00:12:22,666 --> 00:12:25,750
♪

307
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:26,791
[grunts]

308
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:33,416
[TAKUMA]
Distance!

309
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:34,875
[TAKUMA grunts]
The hell?

310
00:12:34,958 --> 00:12:36,000
He's got that whole

311
00:12:36,083 --> 00:12:37,000
"don't give
an enemy an opening"

312
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:38,916
thing down hard!

313
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,083
[gasping]

314
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:43,458
♪

315
00:12:43,541 --> 00:12:45,208
[GALFORD] Looks like
you didn't have to

316
00:12:45,291 --> 00:12:46,666
fight the Elves
to get worn down.

317
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:48,125
Your movements
are rather slow

318
00:12:48,208 --> 00:12:49,416
for a Sorcerer
who defeated

319
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,541
 an army of Fallen,
aren't they?

320
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:52,666
[scoffs]

321
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:54,166
[DIABLO]
It takes a lot of strength

322
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:55,916
to motivate me,
and you're too weak!

323
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,833
♪

324
00:12:57,916 --> 00:12:59,416
[explosion]

325
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:00,458
That's fine.

326
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:01,333
It only makes you

327
00:13:01,416 --> 00:13:02,833
that much easier to read.

328
00:13:02,916 --> 00:13:04,041
Nothing wasted.

329
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:05,333
Hmm.

330
00:13:05,416 --> 00:13:07,375
So you laid
a trap for me, then?

331
00:13:07,458 --> 00:13:09,083
[DIABLO]
It's called Super Mine.

332
00:13:09,166 --> 00:13:10,708
It's a spell planted
in the ground

333
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:13,166
that explodes
when someone steps on it.

334
00:13:15,875 --> 00:13:17,583
You know,
it's been 30 years

335
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:20,125
since anyone's tried
to wound me, Diablo.

336
00:13:20,208 --> 00:13:21,125
How fun.

337
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:22,166
[DIABLO
Sure is.

338
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,125
And you've never

339
00:13:23,208 --> 00:13:24,708
faced a better opponent.

340
00:13:24,791 --> 00:13:26,666
Which is
why you'll lose.

341
00:13:30,708 --> 00:13:32,041
[TAKUMA]
He's keeping me from

342
00:13:32,125 --> 00:13:33,166
reading
his path somehow.

343
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,125
Good call.

344
00:13:34,208 --> 00:13:35,166
However!

345
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:36,208
I happen
to know how to

346
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:37,791
close in
on a Sorcerer,

347
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:40,375
which means
I can also prevent it!

348
00:13:40,458 --> 00:13:42,166
It's called research, Galf!

349
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:43,375
All my shower-less days

350
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:45,083
are about to pay off!

351
00:13:45,166 --> 00:13:46,333
And you don't
wanna mess with me,

352
00:13:46,416 --> 00:13:47,875
Lord Failure!

353
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:49,625
The man standing
before you is one

354
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:51,083
who has sent countless
challengers

355
00:13:51,166 --> 00:13:52,041
to the grave.

356
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:54,083
Diablo,
the Demon Lord!

357
00:13:54,166 --> 00:13:55,166
♪

358
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,666
[explosion]

359
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:58,208
[TAKUMA]
An opening!

360
00:13:58,291 --> 00:14:00,041
[DIABLO echoing]
Freeze Zone!

361
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:02,625
♪

362
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:03,750
[shattering]

363
00:14:06,166 --> 00:14:07,666
[TAKUMA]
It's all over.

364
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,208
Galfie!

365
00:14:09,291 --> 00:14:10,791
[rumbling]

366
00:14:10,875 --> 00:14:11,708
[GALFORD grunts]

367
00:14:11,791 --> 00:14:12,708
[TAKUMA]
What the...

368
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:13,666
Crap,
I can't move

369
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,125
because of my skills recoil!

370
00:14:16,208 --> 00:14:17,875
That turd
created the opening

371
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:20,208
just to draw a bigger
move out of me!

372
00:14:20,291 --> 00:14:21,750
You're better
than I thought,

373
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:22,875
Gal-loser!

374
00:14:22,958 --> 00:14:26,791
♪

375
00:14:26,875 --> 00:14:27,750
[GALFORD grunts]

376
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:31,166
[grunts]

377
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:32,291
[gasp]

378
00:14:32,375 --> 00:14:34,083
[gasp]

379
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:35,541
[groans]

380
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,791
[DIABLO]
One of those was Omit.

381
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:42,208
[DIABLO]
The other was Lightning Bullet.

382
00:14:43,208 --> 00:14:44,708
[TAKUMA]
That was too close.

383
00:14:44,791 --> 00:14:45,833
I didn't think Galford

384
00:14:45,916 --> 00:14:47,375
was capable of
using Martial Arts

385
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:49,041
as his absolute defense.

386
00:14:49,125 --> 00:14:52,125
It worked perfectly
against my attacks.

387
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:53,875
That last skill
was Heat Sonic,

388
00:14:53,958 --> 00:14:55,875
which I learned
around level one-twenty.

389
00:14:55,958 --> 00:14:57,791
That makes him
the most powerful opponent

390
00:14:57,875 --> 00:15:00,333
I've had since
coming to this world.

391
00:15:00,416 --> 00:15:01,750
[groans]

392
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:02,750
[GALFORD]
Aren't you going to

393
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:04,666
kill me now?

394
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:05,625
[GALFORD gags]

395
00:15:05,708 --> 00:15:07,000
[grunts]

396
00:15:07,083 --> 00:15:08,250
[GALFORD]
Guess you didn't realize

397
00:15:08,333 --> 00:15:09,958
I was still alive.

398
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:12,333
[TAKUMA]
Seriously, Old Man?

399
00:15:12,416 --> 00:15:14,125
If he thinks it was
a close match,

400
00:15:14,208 --> 00:15:15,500
he might
change his diapers

401
00:15:15,583 --> 00:15:17,375
and come
after me again.

402
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:19,458
I don't want him
to get fixated.

403
00:15:19,541 --> 00:15:21,791
I guess I should try
and intimidate him more.

404
00:15:21,875 --> 00:15:23,208
[grunts]

405
00:15:23,291 --> 00:15:26,041
[DIABLO laughs]

406
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:28,375
Your weakness made me
lose interest!

407
00:15:29,416 --> 00:15:30,791
I'm dying of boredom.

408
00:15:30,875 --> 00:15:31,833
Someone like you

409
00:15:31,916 --> 00:15:33,125
would never be
a good match!

410
00:15:33,208 --> 00:15:34,416
[GALFORD groans]
Are you going to

411
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:35,541
kill me or not?

412
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:36,791
Perhaps I would
if you were a

413
00:15:36,875 --> 00:15:38,208
normal opponent.

414
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:40,000
But it looks like you
risked it all to strike

415
00:15:40,083 --> 00:15:42,166
while I was frozen
after a huge move.

416
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:44,541
You honestly didn't think

417
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:45,875
I planned for that?

418
00:15:45,958 --> 00:15:46,958
If you're not
strong enough

419
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:48,958
to anticipate
my strategies,

420
00:15:49,041 --> 00:15:50,833
then you're not
a threat to me.

421
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:53,333
Even if I let you live.

422
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:54,291
You sure?

423
00:15:54,375 --> 00:15:55,500
I could still give a report

424
00:15:55,583 --> 00:15:56,750
to His Royal Majesty

425
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:59,041
which would put you
at a disadvantage.

426
00:15:59,125 --> 00:15:59,958
Huh?

427
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:01,083
[ALICIA]
Perhaps.

428
00:16:01,166 --> 00:16:02,916
But I won't allow
that to happen.

429
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:03,875
Sir Galford,

430
00:16:03,958 --> 00:16:05,125
I'm prepared to report

431
00:16:05,208 --> 00:16:06,875
that you took action
with the intent of

432
00:16:06,958 --> 00:16:09,791
destroying our peace
with the surrounding nations.

433
00:16:09,875 --> 00:16:11,291
[GALFORD]
I still say killing me

434
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:13,666
is the only way
to ensure your safety.

435
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:14,666
[DIABLO]
Enough!

436
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:15,583
If you wanna die,

437
00:16:15,666 --> 00:16:16,916
do it on your own!

438
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:18,416
If you wish to challenge me,

439
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,583
I will take you on
at any time.

440
00:16:20,666 --> 00:16:21,583
But,

441
00:16:21,666 --> 00:16:22,875
if you move against me

442
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:24,541
or my possessions again.

443
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:25,916
I will reduce both you

444
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,625
and your land to ash!

445
00:16:27,708 --> 00:16:30,333
♪

446
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:32,416
[groans softly]

447
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:33,500
[footsteps departing]

448
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,666
[GALFORD]
All units, withdraw!

449
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:37,458
[metal suits clanking]

450
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:39,833
[sighs]

451
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:44,666
Galford just went to
pout in the woods.

452
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:47,125
Thanks for making
my entire night.

453
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:48,875
[DIABLO]
You're welcome, Rem.

454
00:16:48,958 --> 00:16:50,708
[giggles softly]

455
00:16:50,791 --> 00:16:52,416
So, hey, do you
have any extra

456
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,541
healing potions
floating around?

457
00:16:54,625 --> 00:16:56,750
[grunts]
Are you injured?

458
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:59,333
[chuckles]
It's actually not for me.

459
00:16:59,416 --> 00:17:00,416
I wanted to use it on

460
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,500
some of the wounded Elves

461
00:17:01,583 --> 00:17:02,958
that aren't that ugly.

462
00:17:03,041 --> 00:17:04,041
[gasps]

463
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:05,083
[DIABLO]
Oh.

464
00:17:05,166 --> 00:17:06,166
Fine.

465
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,583
[giggles softly]
Thanks, yo.

466
00:17:08,666 --> 00:17:10,375
I know you
secretly love them.

467
00:17:10,458 --> 00:17:13,000
[grunts]
Disgusting!

468
00:17:13,083 --> 00:17:14,250
Say that one more time

469
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:16,375
and I'll blow
the entire forest down!

470
00:17:16,458 --> 00:17:18,541
[REM] Why don't you
huff and puff about it first?

471
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:19,833
I'm gonna heal the Elves.

472
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:20,958
I'll tell 'em you said hi.

473
00:17:21,041 --> 00:17:23,666
[groans]
Please don't.

474
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:25,500
-[REM] Real talk?
-Hmm?

475
00:17:27,541 --> 00:17:28,916
Go to Shera.

476
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,958
She needs you right now.

477
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:34,083
♪

478
00:17:35,041 --> 00:17:36,666
[footsteps approaching]

479
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:44,291
[SHERA]
It had to happen, right?

480
00:17:44,375 --> 00:17:45,375
I don't understand

481
00:17:45,458 --> 00:17:47,791
international matters, but...

482
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:50,875
I know Keera
did something bad.

483
00:17:51,833 --> 00:17:52,916
I hated my brother

484
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:55,291
more than I ever
admitted to anyone.

485
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:57,041
[DIABLO grunts]

486
00:17:57,125 --> 00:17:58,291
[SHERA]
But...

487
00:17:59,416 --> 00:18:00,583
I never thought
this would be

488
00:18:00,666 --> 00:18:02,541
the way it ended.

489
00:18:02,625 --> 00:18:05,000
I still lost a part of me.

490
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:08,958
[SHERA crying]

491
00:18:09,041 --> 00:18:13,208
♪

492
00:18:16,250 --> 00:18:17,666
[wailing]

493
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,333
[TAKUMA]
Three days have passed

494
00:18:26,416 --> 00:18:27,375
since we stopped the war

495
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:29,500
between the Elves and Faltra.

496
00:18:29,583 --> 00:18:30,750
Life went on as usual

497
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:32,583
for everyone in the city.

498
00:18:32,666 --> 00:18:33,791
They never even knew

499
00:18:33,875 --> 00:18:36,166
how close they
were to facing danger.

500
00:18:37,541 --> 00:18:39,541
Shera was
upset for a long time.

501
00:18:40,875 --> 00:18:42,166
But Rem
has a way of

502
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:43,958
livening things up.

503
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:46,500
Alicia returned
to her duties

504
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:48,000
and headed
toward the capital

505
00:18:48,083 --> 00:18:49,625
to report
the events in detail

506
00:18:49,708 --> 00:18:52,000
to the emperor.

507
00:18:52,083 --> 00:18:53,125
As for Greenwood,

508
00:18:53,208 --> 00:18:54,583
Celsior took initiative

509
00:18:54,666 --> 00:18:55,708
in explaining matters

510
00:18:55,791 --> 00:18:56,916
to the kingdom.

511
00:18:58,125 --> 00:19:00,666
And I'm just the usual.

512
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:03,000
Over it with
a side of blah.

513
00:19:03,083 --> 00:19:05,041
When my Magic Points
are next to zero,

514
00:19:05,125 --> 00:19:06,083
I can't find the drive

515
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:08,208
to do anything.

516
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:09,083
It would be fine

517
00:19:09,166 --> 00:19:10,583
if that's all it was,

518
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:12,291
but we're also
stupid broke.

519
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:14,541
Frickin' Gal-Dwarf.

520
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:16,125
Even though we
completed the quest

521
00:19:16,208 --> 00:19:18,250
to prevent war
with the Elves,

522
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:19,333
He was our client

523
00:19:19,416 --> 00:19:20,708
and I beat
the crap out of him.

524
00:19:20,791 --> 00:19:22,166
He repaid me
by stiffing us

525
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:23,791
on the reward.

526
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:25,041
Stupid Galford!

527
00:19:25,125 --> 00:19:26,416
I hate your stupid face!

528
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,291
[knocking]

529
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:29,333
[DIABLO]
What?

530
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:30,375
[door opens]

531
00:19:30,458 --> 00:19:32,916
Rise and shine,
Deeb-arooni!

532
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,208
What do you want?

533
00:19:34,291 --> 00:19:35,166
I thought you might be

534
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:36,333
sulking your life away,

535
00:19:36,416 --> 00:19:37,541
so I brought
you something

536
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:38,416
to bring you back.

537
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:39,708
[DIABLO]
An MP potion?

538
00:19:39,791 --> 00:19:40,666
[SYLVIE]
Very close!

539
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:42,291
Except, no.
Even better.

540
00:19:42,375 --> 00:19:44,625
A booze cruise
with this lovely spirit

541
00:19:44,708 --> 00:19:46,875
that has the ability
to recover Magic Points.

542
00:19:46,958 --> 00:19:48,125
[DIABLO]
Never heard of it.

543
00:19:48,208 --> 00:19:49,916
[SYLVIE] Probably because
it's for babies,

544
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,958
but that means
it's tastier than a potion,

545
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:53,875
and it was cheap as hell!

546
00:19:53,958 --> 00:19:55,125
Get up!

547
00:19:55,208 --> 00:19:57,375
Let me fix ya!

548
00:19:57,458 --> 00:19:59,208
[SYLVIE]
Cheers!

549
00:19:59,291 --> 00:20:00,833
[DIABLO]
Yep.

550
00:20:00,916 --> 00:20:02,791
[TAKUMA] So this is
what it's come to, huh?

551
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:06,000
I never got into drinking.

